{"ts":"2026-06-27T15:46:34.102Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Token Storage**\n\nI've discovered the JWT is stored as `gff_ai_access_token` in localStorage. Now, I'm examining `app/portal/support/page.tsx` again. I see it loads tickets from `localStorage` via `localStorage.getItem(\"gff_support_tickets\")`. I need to connect the two concepts.\n\n\n**Designing Ticket APIs**\n\nOkay, I'm now outlining the API endpoints. I am specifying `app/api/v1/support/route.ts` with a `GET` method to list tickets, filtering by `client_id` for regular users and listing all for admins. I'm focusing on \"If comments endpoint exists, allow frontend-only or backend comment based on API availability.\" I need to consider `POST` `/api/v1/support` for ticket creation and comments. I will research support API standards next.\n\n\n**Defining Ticket Creation**\n\nI'm now detailing the structure of the ticket creation process. The `POST` request to create a ticket involves fields such as subject, description, priority, category, linked project and document IDs, with validation required. The system will generate a ticket ID, like `T-xxx` and add the initial message to `wireFeed`. I need to ensure inputs, like subject and description, are not empty. I also am looking at `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts`.\n\n\n**Comparing Ticket Structures**\n\nI'm now comparing the `ClientSupportTicket` structure, used in the client-facing UI, against the `ApiSupportTicket` structure I'm defining for the API. It appears `title` in the client UI aligns with `subject` in the API, which I need to reconcile. Additionally, I need to understand the relationship between `SupportTicket` and its extension, `ClientSupportTicket`. I'm focusing on the differences between `ApiSupportTicket` versus `ClientSupportTicket` because the UI uses `ClientSupportTicket`.\n\n\n**Clarifying Ticket Fields**\n\nI'm now tracing the usage of ticket fields across the application. I noticed in the UI, `title` maps from `SupportTicket`. I've examined `previewSupportTickets` and `INITIAL_TICKETS` more closely. It seems that `title` and `replies` are used in the client portal, which imports `previewSupportTickets` from `lib/mock-data-model.ts`, while `subject` and `wireFeed` are used in the admin portal's `INITIAL_TICKETS`. I need to figure out if these refer to the same logical data, even though they come from different sources.\n\n\n"}}
