{"ts":"2026-06-27T15:47:13.835Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Identifying Relevant Files**\n\nI've begun by identifying files needing modification. Specifically, I've noted `app/portal/support/page.tsx` as starting the process, and I'm adding `app/portal/support/[id]/page.tsx` to the list of impacted files. My focus is on compiling a complete list of relevant code to ensure all bases are covered.\n\n\n**Expanding File Considerations**\n\nI've expanded the scope to include `app/api/v1/support/route.ts` and `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts`, which are new API files, as I double-checked and they don't exist yet. Before diving into code, I'm now drafting an internal design plan per the request, iterating on page narrative, visual metaphor, and other core aspects of the approach. The design plan is taking shape!\n\n\n**Defining Interaction Paradigms**\n\nI'm solidifying the interaction paradigms for the new support interface. This includes real-time API feedback loops for ticket listings and submissions, complete with elegant loading overlays, empty states, and robust error callouts with retry buttons. Secure form validation and success notifications will be added. The mobile strategy is also defined and I'm ensuring seamless column stacking for smaller screens.\n\n\n**Confirming Mobile Responsiveness**\n\nI'm now focusing on mobile optimization, ensuring the support interface will render smoothly on touch devices. I've confirmed column stacking and usability on smaller viewports. I'm also confirming specific files like `app/api/v1/support/route.ts`, `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts`, `app/portal/support/page.tsx`, and `app/portal/support/[id]/page.tsx` are where the main changes must occur. I am confident I will avoid unneeded edits to landing pages and GFF AI tools. I am now working on understanding backend ticket API access controls.\n\n\n**Analyzing API Authorization**\n\nI am now closely analyzing the existing API authorization scheme, specifically how access tokens and user roles are verified. I've focused on understanding the JWT decoding process and user authentication within `lib/api-auth.ts`. I am also examining the `ApiSupportTicket` structure, including the `WireFeed` array with its message properties. My goal is to ensure that the modifications I make will align with the existing security and data structures.\n\n\n**Verifying Mock Data**\n\nI'm now focusing on ensuring that my modifications are fully compatible with existing mock data and API endpoints. I am reviewing how the `category` field is used in `app/portal/support/page.tsx` and verifying that my API calls in `/api/v1/support/route.ts` correctly handle these categories. I am also confirming the secure access control logic within this file. Specifically, I need to ensure that the mocked support ticket data, exported from `lib/api-auth.ts`, aligns perfectly with the updated data structure.\n\n\n**Implementing API Endpoints**\n\nNow, I'm designing the `GET` and `POST` methods for `app/api/v1/support/route.ts`. The `GET` method will include an authorization check, and I'll return tickets as `{ success: true, tickets: Array }`, filtered by client association. The `POST` will handle ticket creation, with validation and a new ticket ID generation, and return an error if invalid, along with a 400 status. I will map priority appropriately. I've confirmed that `API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS` is exported.\n\n\n**Mapping Priority Levels**\n\nI'm now mapping priority levels from various inputs to the standard \"P1\", \"P2\", and \"P3\" values within `ApiSupportTicket`. The code will be flexible enough to handle different priority input formats. I've designed logic to ensure compatibility and standard field usage for ticket data. I will be handling the ticket save logic to persist the data to the system.\n\n\n**Synchronizing Data Fields**\n\nI'm now synchronizing `wireFeed` and `replies` to ensure compatibility between the admin and client support UIs. When a new ticket is added, or an existing ticket is updated, the API routes will automatically populate both fields. I will handle this logic in `app/api/v1/support/route.ts` and `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts`.\n\n\n**Synchronizing Data Fields**\n\nI'm now synchronizing `wireFeed` and `replies` to ensure compatibility between the admin and client support UIs. When a new ticket is added, or an existing ticket is updated, the API routes will automatically populate both fields, and that will make my life easy as the code and architecture become rock solid. I've designed and am implementing this logic in `app/api/v1/support/route.ts` and `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts`, with conditional mapping to synchronize these fields. I'm taking the senior level design approach!\n\n\n**Defining Comment Endpoints**\n\nI'm now focusing on implementing the backend comment endpoint. I'll include a `POST` method in `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts` to add comments, and a parallel `/comments` endpoint, as well. The GET method will return ticket details, and POST adds comments to `wireFeed` and `replies`, updating the status to `IN_PROGRESS` or `INVESTIGATING` if a comment is added, all from the backend.\n\n\n**Drafting Comment Endpoints**\n\nI'm now drafting the `POST` method for the comment functionality in `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts`. The API endpoint's input will be validated, ensuring that text is provided. Then the comment will be added to both `wireFeed` and `replies`. I am planning to generate a mock bot response in the backend, mirroring a system interaction.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T15:47:13.838Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"rknq8ji4","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/support/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, \n  API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS, \n  verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, \n  ApiSupportTicket, \n  getClientIdFromAssociation,\n  getClientNameFromId\n} from \"../../../../lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Missing/malformed Authorization header.\" };\n  }\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Invalid/expired access token.\" };\n  }\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  if (!user) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Authorized user not found.\" };\n  }\n  if (user.status === \"inactive\") {\n    return { status: 403, error: \"Forbidden\", msg: \"This account is inactive.\" };\n  }\n  return { caller: user };\n}\n\nexport async function GET(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    const { searchParams } = new URL(req.url);\n    const clientIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"client_id\");\n    const categoryFilter = searchParams.get(\"category\");\n    const priorityFilter = searchParams.get(\"priority\");\n    const statusFilter = searchParams.get(\"status\");\n    const searchQuery = searchParams.get(\"search\");\n\n    let tickets = Object.values(API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS) as ApiSupportTicket[];\n\n    // Ensure bidirectional mapping of wireFeed and replies\n    tickets = tickets.map(t => {\n      const ticketWithReplies = { ...t } as any;\n      if (t.wireFeed && !ticketWithReplies.replies) {\n        ticketWithReplies.replies = t.wireFeed.map(w => ({\n          sender: w.senderName,\n          text: w.text,\n          timestamp: w.timestamp.includes(\"Z\") || w.timestamp.includes(\"-\") ? w.timestamp : new Date().toISOString()\n        }));\n      }\n      return ticketWithReplies;\n    });\n\n    // RBAC policy logic\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      const callerClientId = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.client_id === callerClientId);\n\n      // Enforce client boundaries\n      if (clientIdFilter && clientIdFilter !== callerClientId) {\n        return NextResponse.json(\n          { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied to requested client's support tickets.\" },\n          { status: 403 }\n        );\n      }\n    } else {\n      // Admin filter\n      if (clientIdFilter) {\n        tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.client_id === clientIdFilter);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Apply specific filters\n    if (categoryFilter) {\n      const q = categoryFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.category.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n    }\n    if (priorityFilter) {\n      const q = priorityFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.priority.toLowerCase() === q || (t as any).priority_label?.toLowerCase() === q);\n    }\n    if (statusFilter) {\n      const q = statusFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.status.toLowerCase() === q);\n    }\n    if (searchQuery) {\n      const q = searchQuery.toLowerCase().trim();\n      tickets = tickets.filter(t => \n        t.subject.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        t.description.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        t.id.toLowerCase().includes(q)\n      );\n    }\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, tickets });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function POST(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    const body = await req.json();\n    const { subject, title, description, desc, priority, category, projectId, linkedProjectId, linkedDocId } = body;\n\n    const finalSubject = subject || title;\n    const finalDescription = description || desc;\n\n    // Secure inputs validation\n    if (!finalSubject?.trim() || !finalDescription?.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Validation Error\", message: \"Summary subject and description are required.\" },\n        { status: 400 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const client_id = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n    const client_name = getClientNameFromId(client_id);\n    const newId = `T-${Math.floor(800 + Math.random() * 200)}`;\n\n    const finalPriority = (priority === \"critical\" || priority === \"high\" ? \"P1\" : priority === \"medium\" ? \"P2\" : \"P3\");\n    const finalCategory = category || \"General\";\n\n    const timestampStr = new Date().toISOString();\n    const wireFeedTime = new Date().toLocaleTimeString([], { hour: '2-digit', minute: '2-digit' });\n\n    const newTicket: any = {\n      id: newId,\n      subject: finalSubject,\n      client_id,\n      client_name,\n      priority: finalPriority,\n      category: finalCategory,\n      status: \"OPEN\",\n      assignedAgent: \"Unassigned\",\n      linkedProjectId: linkedProjectId || projectId || undefined,\n      linkedDocId: linkedDocId || undefined,\n      slaSeconds: 14400, // default 4 hour SLA\n      description: finalDescription,\n      createdDate: timestampStr,\n      wireFeed: [\n        {\n          id: \"w1\",\n          sender: \"client\",\n          senderName: caller.name,\n          text: finalDescription,\n          timestamp: wireFeedTime\n        }\n      ],\n      replies: [\n        {\n          sender: caller.name + \" (Client)\",\n          text: finalDescription,\n          timestamp: timestampStr\n        }\n      ]\n    };\n\n    // Save ticket in-memory (and also locally)\n    API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS[newId.toLowerCase()] = newTicket;\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, ticket: newTicket }, { status: 201 });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
