{"ts":"2026-06-27T15:53:27.706Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"mx7asmty","input":{"summary":"Successfully connected the Client Support Portal (`/portal/support` and its dynamic detail route `/portal/support/[id]`) to newly built robust backend SLA support ticket APIs.\n\n### What was done:\n1. **Designed & Created Support Tickets API (`app/api/v1/support/route.ts`)**:\n   - `GET`: Retreives all tickets for the authenticated client. Implements RBAC filtering so client users only see their own tickets, while admins can see everything.\n   - `POST`: Validates and creates a new support ticket with client context mapping and automatically opens the initial wire log block.\n2. **Designed & Created Individual Ticket Detail API (`app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts`)**:\n   - `GET`: Returns the active SLA details and full thread logs.\n   - `POST`: Decodes VPN handshake text, appends client comments, and registers automated high-fidelity system/architect responses custom-tailored to the ticket's category (e.g. AI Operations, Billing, Governance).\n3. **Integrated Support Portal Frontends**:\n   - **Ticket List (`app/portal/support/page.tsx`)**: Replaced offline localStorage mockups with dynamic async API fetching. Integrated premium loading state skeletons, detailed connection failure panels with retry buttons, robust form input validation, and successful registration toast alerts.\n   - **Ticket Details (`app/portal/support/[id]/page.tsx`)**: Upgraded to dynamic API fetching based on parameters. Added full-page loading indicators, error recovery handshakes, and connected reply inputs directly to the comments post handler.\n4. **Validation Done**:\n   - Executed `npx eslint app/portal/support` which returned 0 warnings/errors.\n   - Executed `npx tsc --noEmit` which compiled successfully with 0 errors.\n\nAll premium aesthetics and layout structures have been completely preserved and polished.","verified":true}}}
